# Deploy after changes

When you finish implementing requested changes in this project:

1. Run `npm run build` and fix any failures before committing.
2. Commit with a clear message (only when there are changes to commit).
3. Push to `origin/main` — Vercel deploys automatically from `main`.
4. Confirm push succeeded (`git status` clean, branch up to date with remote).
5. Briefly tell the user the commit was pushed and deploy is in progress on Vercel.

Do not skip push/deploy unless the user explicitly asks not to, or there are no code changes.
